{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2014}}
Sneider started his career working in many different aspects of production, including being a Location Manager, Production Manager, and assistant director. His credits include films such as ''[[Havana (film)|Havana]]'' ([[Sidney Pollack]]), ''Gringo Viejo'' (Luis Puenzo), ''[[Blood In Blood Out|Blood In, Blood Out]]'' ([[Taylor Hackford]]) and ''[[Mi Vida Loca]]'' ([[Allison Anders]]).<ref name=about/>
Sneider produced and directed “[[Tear This Heart Out|Arráncame la Vida]]”, a period drama based on the novel of the same name by Ángeles Mastretta.  With critically acclaimed performances by [[Ana Claudia Talancón]] and [[Daniel Giménez Cacho]], it was Mexico's official submission for the 2009 [[Academy Awards|Academy Award]] for Best Foreign Language Film and is one of the highest grossing Mexican films ever.<ref>{{cite web| url = https://www.forbes.com.mx/las-15-peliculas-mexicanas-mas-taquilleras-de-la-historia/| title = Las 15 películas mexicanas más taquilleras de la historia • Forbes México| date = July 19, 2013}}</ref> It won three Mexican Academy awards.<ref name=about/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2009/film/awards/nine-vie-for-foreign-language-oscar-1117998446/|title=Nine vie for foreign language Oscar|date=January 13, 2009}}</ref>

