{{Redirect-distinguish|Champac|Champak}}
In the province of [[Aceh]], [[Indonesia]], the champak flower ({{Langx|ace|bungong jeumpa}}) is highly revered in [[Acehnese people|Acehnese]] culture, being seen as the flower of Aceh as a whole.<ref name=":12">{{Cite web |last=Redaksi |date=2022-12-26 |title=Bungong Jeumpa dalam Budaya Aceh |url=https://leughok.com/bungong-jeumpa-aceh/ |access-date=2025-07-30 |website=LEUGHOK.COM |language=id}}</ref><ref name=":32">{{Cite web |last=Serambi |first=Wahana News |date=2021-11-26 |title=Cempaka Kuning Flora Khas dari Provinsi Aceh |url=https://serambi.wahananews.co/khas/cempaka-kuning-flora-khas-dari-provinsi-aceh/1 |access-date=2025-07-30 |website=Wahana News Serambi |language=id}}</ref> It's used as a symbol of beauty,<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |last=Lissafrina |date=28 June 2024 |title=Mengenal Bungong Jeumpa yang Jadi Kebanggaan Masyarakat Aceh |trans-title=Getting to Know the Pride of the Acehnese People, the Champak Flower |url=https://rri.co.id/daerah/786512/mengenal-bungong-jeumpa-yang-jadi-kebanggaan-masyarakat-aceh |access-date=30 July 2025 |website=rri.co.id}}</ref> commonly seen in rituals or used as [[Ornamental plant|ornaments]].<ref name=":32"/><ref name=":2">{{Cite web |last= |date=2 September 2023 |title=Tari Bungong Jeumpa: Asal-usul, Makna, Lirik, dan Gerakan |url=https://www.cnnindonesia.com/edukasi/20230824143207-569-990018/tari-bungong-jeumpa-asal-usul-makna-lirik-dan-gerakan |access-date=30 July 2025 |website=www.cnnindonesia.com |place=Jakarta}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=LindungiHutan |first=Magang Alam |date=2023-07-31 |title=Bunga Cempaka: Tanaman Hijau Abadi Khas Aceh |url=https://lindungihutan.com/blog/mengenal-bunga-cempaka/ |access-date=2025-07-30 |language=en-US}}</ref> An Acehnese [[Folk music|folk song]] titled {{Lang|ace|[[Bungong Jeumpa]]}} ({{Literal translation|Champak Flower}}) sings about its beauty and characteristics.
*Fernando, M. Thilina R., et al. "Identifying dormancy class and storage behaviour of champak (Magnolia champaca) seeds, an important tropical timber tree." Journal of the National Science Foundation of Sri Lanka 41.2 (2013): 141–146.

