'''St. Andrew's Church''' is a [[parish church]] in the [[Church of England]] in [[Skegby]], [[Nottinghamshire]]. The church is [[Grade II listed]] by the [[Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport]]<ref name=scheduling>{{National Heritage List for England |num=1234873 |desc=CHURCH OF ST ANDREW, MANSFIELD ROAD|accessdate=4 January 2014}}</ref> as it is a building of special architectural or historic interest.
[[File:Skegby War Memorial, Near entrance to St Andrews Church, Mansfield Road, Skegby (4).jpg|thumb|200px|Skegby War Memorial, Near entrance to St Andrews Church (Grade II listed)]]

{{Use Hiberno-English|date=October 2021}}
'''Barnane''' ({{Irish place name|An Bearnán}}) is a [[townland]] in the [[Civil parishes in Ireland|civil parish]] of the same name in [[County Tipperary]], [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Placenames Database of Ireland|url=http://www.logainm.ie/46742.aspx|publisher=Dublin City University|accessdate=3 February 2015}}</ref> Barnane or '''Barnane-Ely''' is one of eleven civil parishes in the historical [[Barony (Ireland)|barony]] of [[Ikerrin]]. It is also part of the [[Ecclesiastical parish]] of [[Drom and Inch]].
The townland gets its name from the legend of [[Saint Patrick]] who was pursuing the Devil out of Ireland. In his haste to escape the ''Apostle of Ireland'', the Devil took a bite out of the mountain. The resultant gap ({{langx|ga|Bearnán}}) is what we see today in an otherwise smooth, table-like mountain. Spitting it out again, the "bit" landed in South Tipperary and formed the [[Rock of Cashel]].{{citation needed|date=November 2021}}
'''The Old School in Barnane (1846–1958)'''
'''The New School in Barnane (1958–present)'''
Barnane National School was built in 1958 by Bertie Keane. To date four Principal teachers have worked in the school. Mrs. Mary White was principal of Barnane old School (1951–1959) and principal of Barnane New School (1959–1988), Mr. Martin Ryan was principal of Barnane N.S. 1988–2004, Mrs. Clare Hanley principal from 2004 to 2020. The current principal is Ms. Therese Glendon (2020–present).<ref>{{Cite web |title=Barnane NS - Our History |url=https://www.barnanens.ie/our-history/ |access-date=2023-07-18 |language=en-US}}</ref>

