{{bots|deny=Citation bot}}
The 1851 and 1861 Censuses find Turner and his wife and son living in Beech Cottage, next to [[Starbeck railway station]], and he is describing himself as a "house and land proprietor".<ref name="1851 England Census Starbeck" >{{cite web |title=1851 England Census, Beech Cottage, Starbeck, HO/107/2283, page 23 |url=https://www.ancestry.co.uk/imageviewer/collections/8860/images/YRKHO107_2283_2283-0401?ssrc=&backlabel=Return&pId=13870066 |website=ancestry.co.uk |publisher=H.M. Government |access-date=13 February 2023 |url-access=subscription}}</ref><ref name="1861 England Census Starbeck" >{{cite web |title=1861 England Census, Scriven with Tentergate (Starbeck), RG/9/3205, page 5, schedule 48 |url=https://www.ancestry.co.uk/imageviewer/collections/8767/images/WRYRG9_3205_3207-0053?ssrc=&backlabel=Return&pId=16390338 |website=ancestry.co.uk |publisher=H.M. Government |access-date=13 February 2023 |url-access=subscription}}</ref> By 1871 Turner is calling his cottage "Beech Villa", and describing himself as a retired draper.<ref>{{cite web |title=1871 England Census, Beech Villa, Knaresborough Road, Bilton with Harrogate (Starbeck), RG10/4291, page 6 |url=https://www.ancestry.co.uk/imageviewer/collections/7619/images/WRYRG10_4288_4291-0605?backlabel=ReturnSearchResults&queryId=1d11d3e23a3146e4885bd49ab822a975&pId=25429724 |website=ancestry.co.uk |publisher=H.M. Government |access-date=14 February 2023}}</ref> In 1881, the Census finds Turner, aged 81, boarding (not visiting) in a lodging house at 5 Promenade Square, in the parish of St Mary's in Low Harrogate.<ref>{{cite web |title=1881 England Census, 5 Promenade Square, St Mary's parish, Low Harrogate (listed as Pannal), RG11/4326, page 2 |url=https://www.ancestry.co.uk/imageviewer/collections/7572/images/WRYRG11_4324_4327-0670?ssrc=&backlabel=Return&pId=23797296 |website=ancestry.co.uk |publisher=H.M. Government |access-date=14 February 2023}}</ref> Meanwhile, his wife Jane was still living in Beech Villa, calling herself a "house and land proprietor's wife".<ref>{{cite web |title=1881 England Census, Beech Villa, Starbeck (Harrogate), RG11/4328, page 7, schedule 105 |url=https://www.ancestry.co.uk/imageviewer/collections/7572/images/WRYRG11_4327_4331-0295?ssrc=&backlabel=Return&pId=23808322 |website=ancestry.co.uk |publisher=H.M. Government |access-date=14 February 2023}}</ref>
{{DEFAULTSORT:Turner, John (miser)}}

