Olszowski was born in [[Olszowa, Łódź Voivodeship|Olszowa]]. He was provost of the [[Poznań]] cathedral chapter (1657–1667) and a Crown Deputy Chancellors in 1666–1676.<ref>Rodzina, herbarz szlachty polskie, t. XII, Warszawa 1915, s. 331.</ref> He died in [[Gdańsk]].
3. Polish speeches from 1649 to 1676 and others, ed.: J. S. Pisarski, {{lang|pl|Mowca polski}}, vol. 2, Kalisz 1676; J. Daneykowicz Ostrowski, Polish and Latin swada, vol. 1, Lublin 1745
4.Latin Speeches from 1665 to 1674 and others, ed. J. C. Luenig, {{lang|la|Orationes procerum Europae}}, Vol. 2, Leipzig 1713; some speeches then came out separately; see Estreicher XXIII, 341-348

