diff_added:
{{aI-generated|date=January 2026}}
Tirkey serves as an assistant professor in the Department of Hindi at [[Ram Lakhan Singh Yadav College]], affiliated with [[Ranchi University]].<ref name=":0" /> Her academic and literary work explores the convergence of tribal oral traditions, folk songs, and modern Hindi poetry, seeking to bridge indigenous experiences with mainstream literary discourse.{{citation needed|date=June 2025}}
Tirkey's first poetry collection, ''Phir Ugna'', was published by Radhakrishna Prakashan in 2023. The collection has been noted{{by whom|date=February 2026}} for its sensitive, direct, and communicative style.{{citation needed|date=February 2026}} Through her poetry, Tirkey brings to life a world populated by earth, trees, birds, forests, and celestial elements, not merely as metaphors but as living presences.<ref name=":0" />
Parvati Tirkey has featured in a BBC documentary where she talks about her life and influences: "Parvati Tirkey: The Sahitya Akademi winner preserving Kurukh culture through poetry"<ref>{{Cite web |last=News India |first=BBC |date=3 October 2025 |title=Parvati Tirkey: The Sahitya Akademi winner preserving Kurukh culture through poetry |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HIOSR3D_SQc |access-date=3 October 2025| website=BBC News India YouTube }}</ref>

