'''''Weaponology''''' is a [[documentary film|documentary]] television series that premiered on November 6, 2007, on the [[Discovery Channel]]. The program also airs on the Military Channel (now [[American Heroes Channel]]). The documentary series was narrated by [[John Schwab]].
Tim Goodman of the ''[[San Francisco Chronicle]]'' wrote that ''Weaponology'' "reminded me—starkly—that I really need to go 'around the horn' more often to discover what's on".<ref name="Goodman2008-04-23">{{cite news |last=Goodman |first=Tim |date=2008-04-23 |title=Winnowing down TV choices reveals some hidden gems |newspaper=[[San Francisco Chronicle]] |id={{Factiva|VENTCS0020080423e44n0000n}} }}</ref> Jasmin Orr of ''[[The Courier-Mail]]'' called the show's second-season premiere "a tad disturbing" when firearms experts and historians express excitement about the sniper rifle [[Accuracy International AS50]]'s lethal capabilities.<ref name="newsbank_11A441E21723B4C0">{{cite news |last=Orr |first=Jasmin |date=2007-07-09 |title=Television Monday |url=https://infoweb.newsbank.com/apps/news/document-view?p=WORLDNEWS&docref=news/11A441E21723B4C0&f=basic |newspaper=[[The Courier-Mail]] |id={{ProQuest|353970050}} |accessdate=2025-09-01 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20250901005301/https://infoweb.newsbank.com/apps/news/document-view?p=WORLDNEWS&docref=news/11A441E21723B4C0&f=basic |archivedate=2025-09-01 }}</ref> In a negative review, ''[[The Age]]'' television critic Brad Newsome said the show had "many layers of inanity" including "fatuous narration", "ill-conceived, computer-generated 3D 'family tree' of sniping that whirls around confusingly in between segments", and "censorship of death itself".<ref name="Newsom2007-07-05">{{cite news |last=Newsome |first=Brad |date=2007-07-05 |title=Television MondayMonday - Pay TV |url=https://infoweb.newsbank.com/apps/news/document-view?p=WORLDNEWS&docref=news/11A2F31C80D52280&f=basic |newspaper=[[The Age]] |id={{ProQuest|364051434}} |accessdate=2025-09-01 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20250901005315/https://infoweb.newsbank.com/apps/news/document-view?p=WORLDNEWS&docref=news/11A2F31C80D52280&f=basic |archivedate=2025-09-01 }}</ref>
The first season of the show primarily covers the history of weapons, including [[tank]]s and [[sniper rifles]]. The second season focuses on [[special operation|special operations groups]], such as the Russian [[Spetsnaz]] American [[Special Forces (United States Army)|Green Berets]], and the British [[Special Air Service]], or [[combat engineers]].{{citation needed|date=September 2025}}

