After his baseball playing career, Whitmer worked in the [[Detroit Tigers]] organization. After starting the 1984 season playing for the Tigers' Double-A farm team, the [[Birmingham Barons]], he was named the bullpen catcher for the eventual [[1984 Detroit Tigers season|1984 World Series champions]] on June 15. He was also the team's bullpen coach from 1992 to 1994.<ref>[http://www.thebaseballcube.com/managers/19628.shtml Dan Whitmer Managing and Coaching History from The Baseball Cube]</ref>

