In 2004, Hunt became a member of the supergroup [[Dark New Day]], and then later [[Evanescence]]. Guitarist Brian Milner went on to join [[Dope (band)|Dope]] as their bassist. Billy Keeton has continued to pursue his musical career with various projects, such as the short-lived Blessed in Black (featuring former members of [[Nothingface (band)|Nothingface]]). Keeton also has contributed vocals for local Florida [[cover band]] Money Shot when not working with former members of [[Primer 55]] Bobby Burns ([[Soulfly]]) and Kobie Jackson. Formerly titled Paris is Burning, the three have named the project King Street. Keeton currently is vocalist for [[Audiotopsy (band)|Audiotopsy]], which features bassist Perry Stern as well as drummer [[Matthew McDonough]] and guitarist [[Greg Tribbett]] of [[Mudvayne]].
After more than two decades of inactivity, Keeton announced on March 8, 2026, that Skrape has reunited and they are planning on touring and releasing new music.<ref name="themosh"/>
* {{AllMusic|class=artist|id=p474312|label=Skrape}}

